   "text":"There were fireworks going off downtown due to the Fourth of July celebration.  I was on a roof 3 stories high.  On the opposite side of the sky from the fireworks we seen multiple shooting stars.  The odd thing is that the shooting stars were changing colors as the hit the atmosphere.  Blue, red, purple, etc.  Then that's when I seen the spacecraft.  I knew right away because how fast it was and how bright it was..  It was bright like the sun, but not blinding.  It looked like a cartoon.  It was yellow like the sponge Bob square pants cartoon.  That's how I knew it was out of this world.   Also, it wasn't oval, disk, saucer, cigar..  Nothing of the norm I hear about UFO..  It was a spider shaped craft.. It had legs like a spider.  The spider feature was phenomenal to me.   Me and my friend looked at each other and confirmed we seen a cartoon spider flying across the sky.  I will never forget.  It is as good as it gets for a belief that something is out there that isn't human",
